<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <div class="faq-head">
      <div class="eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">// faq.md</div>
      <h2 class="h2">The questions every operator asks us.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list" id="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item open">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q1</span>Will it sound like a robot? My customers will hate that.</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>No. Modern AI voice (built on the same tech behind ChatGPT Voice and ElevenLabs) is indistinguishable from a human in the first 30 seconds — and most calls end inside 30 seconds because we book the job that fast. We've A/B tested this with hundreds of operators. Your customers won't know.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q2</span>What happens if the AI can't handle a call?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>It transfers. Every plan includes intelligent escalation — if a customer asks something outside scope (warranty dispute, complex commercial bid, etc.), the AI routes the call to your cell, your office, or whoever you designate. Zero dropped calls.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q3</span>Do I have to switch from ServiceTitan / Jobber / Housecall Pro?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>No. We integrate with all major home service CRMs and dispatch tools. If you have something custom, we build the integration. Your existing workflow doesn't change — it just gets more leads in the top of it.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q4</span>What if I'm a one-truck operation?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Starter plan is built for you. Most of our solo operators recover their first month's cost in week one. The smaller you are, the more every missed call hurts — and the more you need this.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q5</span>How is this different from a regular answering service?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Answering services cost $300–$600/month, take a message, and forget you exist. Our AI books the job, schedules the appointment, sends the confirmation, and follows up if the customer ghosts. It's the difference between a secretary and a sales rep.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q6</span>What's the catch?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>Honestly, the catch is your tolerance for change. The AI works. It books jobs. The biggest reason operators don't see results is they don't forward their phone line because they're nervous. We hold your hand through week one to make sure that doesn't happen.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q"><span><span class="faq-num">Q7</span>Refund policy?</span><span class="faq-plus">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p>30 days. If your AI doesn't book at least 10 jobs in your first 30 days, full refund — including setup. We've never had to issue one. Doesn't mean we won't, but the offer's bulletproof for a reason.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

